library(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)
daily_aqi <- read_csv("data/akl-aqi19.csv")
aqi_cat <- fct_inorder(c("Good", "Moderate", "Unhealthy for Sensitive",
  "Unhealthy", "Very Unhealthy", "Hazardous"))
aqi_pal <- setNames(
  c("#00E400", "#FFFF00", "#FF7E00", "#FF0000", "#8F3F97", "#7E0023"),
  aqi_cat)
rng <- c(0, 50, 100, 150, 200, 300, Inf)

daily_aqi <- daily_aqi %>% 
  mutate(aqi_cat = cut(max_aqi, breaks = rng, include.lowest = TRUE, labels = aqi_cat),
         month = month(date, label = TRUE),
         mday = mday(date)
         ) 
         
daily_aqi

Question 1

aqi_table <- daily_aqi %>% 
  group_by(month, aqi_cat, .drop = FALSE) %>% 
  summarise(count = n()) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = aqi_cat, values_from = count) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  rename(Month = month)
  
kable(aqi_table)

Question 2

aqi_heatmap <- daily_aqi %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = mday, y = month))+
  geom_tile(aes(fill = aqi_cat), height = 0.95, width = 0.95) + 
  geom_text(aes(label = max_aqi), size = 3) +
  coord_fixed()+ 
  theme_minimal() + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = aqi_pal, drop = FALSE) +
  scale_y_discrete(limits = rev(levels(daily_aqi$month)), expand = expansion()) + 
  theme(legend.position = "top") + 
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(10,20,30), expand = expansion()) + 
  guides(fill = guide_legend(nrow = 1, title = "AQI")) + 
  labs(x = "Day of the Month", y = "Month")

aqi_heatmap

In the second half of the year, the primary influence on the air quality was the Australian bush fires.
